  "text": "DPP-IV is expressed in the human liver, intestine, and kidney; in particular, DPP-IV is highly expressed in the apical brush border surface of proximal renal tubular cells [CITATION_1] . However, it is unclear whether the inhibition of DPP-IV affects the pathogenesis of renal disease.",
